.TH OD "1" "April 2026" "GNU coreutils 9.11" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
od \- dump files in octal and other formats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B od
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,FILE\/\fR]...
.br
.B od
[\fI\,-abcdfilosx\/\fR]... [\fI\,FILE\/\fR] [[\fI\,+\/\fR]\fI\,OFFSET\/\fR[\fI\,.\/\fR][\fI\,b\/\fR]]
.br
.B od
\fI\,--traditional \/\fR[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,FILE\/\fR] [[\fI\,+\/\fR]\fI\,OFFSET\/\fR[\fI\,.\/\fR][\fI\,b\/\fR] [\fI\,+\/\fR][\fI\,LABEL\/\fR][\fI\,.\/\fR][\fI\,b\/\fR]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Write an unambiguous representation, octal bytes by default,
of FILE to standard output.  With more than one FILE argument,
concatenate them in the listed order to form the input.
.PP
With no FILE, or when FILE is \-, read standard input.
.PP
If first and second call formats both apply, the second format is assumed
if the last operand begins with + or (if there are 2 operands) a digit.
An OFFSET operand means \fB\-j\fR OFFSET.  LABEL is the pseudo\-address
at first byte printed, incremented when dump is progressing.
For OFFSET and LABEL, a 0x or 0X prefix indicates hexadecimal;
suffixes may be . for octal and b for multiply by 512.
.PP
Mandatory arguments to long options are mandatory for short options too.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-A'\fB\-A, \-\-address\-radix=\,RADIX\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
output format for file offsets;
RADIX is one of [doxn], for Decimal, Octal, Hex or None
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od--endian'\fB\-\-endian={big|little}\fP\X'tty: link'
swap input bytes according the specified order
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-j'\fB\-j, \-\-skip\-bytes=\,BYTES\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
skip BYTES input bytes first
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-N'\fB\-N, \-\-read\-bytes=\,BYTES\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
limit dump to BYTES input bytes
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-S'\fB\-S BYTES, \-\-strings[=\,BYTES]\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
show only NUL terminated strings
of at least BYTES (default 3) printable characters
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-t'\fB\-t, \-\-format=\,TYPE\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
select output format or formats
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-v'\fB\-v, \-\-output\-duplicates\fP\X'tty: link'
do not use * to mark line suppression
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od-w'\fB\-w[BYTES], \-\-width[=\,BYTES]\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
output BYTES bytes per output line;
32 is implied when BYTES is not specified
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#od--traditional'\fB\-\-traditional\fP\X'tty: link'
accept arguments in third form above
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/od#od--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
